{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"feminine-goodly-koi","description":"# Publish governance: GOVERNANCE.md, MAINTAINERS.md, CoC contact fix (CODEOWNERS explicitly skipped)\n\n## Why\n\nGovernance is implicit today; an outsider cannot see who decides, how maintainers are added, or where a Code of Conduct report goes if it concerns the maintainer himself. Peer convergence (curl's GOVERNANCE.md, the CNCF small-project template, opensource.guide) gives a one-page recipe. The one thing no template covers — and the thing readers of an org-backed solo project will probe — is the Nava-PBC-backed-but-individual-led ambiguity, so it gets its own section.\n\n## What\n\n- `GOVERNANCE.md` (~1 page) with the seven convergent sections:\n  1. Overview — maintainer-led, created and stewarded at Nava PBC; name the current lead maintainer. Use \"lead maintainer\" language, not \"BDFL\" (same authority, role language that survives a handoff and fits the org-backed story — decision recorded).\n  2. Roles — contributor / maintainer / lead maintainer, with rebar-specific powers spelled out: Gerrit submit rights, ticket-store write access, release authority.\n  3. Decision-making — consensus among maintainers; the lead maintainer has final say (curl's model in maintainer-led language); routine technical decisions happen in Gerrit review and rebar tickets.\n  4. Becoming a maintainer — sustained quality contributions through Gerrit review (\"a few quality changes merged as proof\" — curl's concrete bar), invited by the lead maintainer.\n  5. Stepping down / emeritus — inactivity → access removed for security reasons, explicitly non-punitive, listed as emeritus.\n  6. Nava PBC's role — what the org provides (Gerrit host, maintainer employment) and what it does NOT control (contributors participate as individuals, per the CNCF framing).\n  7. Changing this document — via the normal Gerrit review process, lead maintainer approves.\n  Plus a one-line \"review happens on Gerrit; GitHub is a read-only mirror\" reorientation near the top (every peer template assumes PRs).\n- `MAINTAINERS.md`: table (name, GitHub handle, Gerrit username, scope, affiliation) with one row today; empty \"Emeritus maintainers\" section as a placeholder; \"changes to this file are proposed as a Gerrit change — see GOVERNANCE.md\". Kept as a separate file (health-file scanners look for it by name) despite the single row.\n- `CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md`: keep the Contributor Covenant; fix the enforcement contact to be role-based with a Nava backstop, adding: \"if a report concerns the lead maintainer, contact <Nava contact> instead.\" Assess the CC 2.1 → 3.0 upgrade (3.0 is the 2026 default — Django/Mastodon/Hanami adopted; nice-to-have, not a blocker) and record the decision either way.\n- Record the explicit non-goal: NO `.github/CODEOWNERS` — it only auto-requests reviewers and gates merges on GitHub PRs, which rebar bot-closes; it would be dead config falsely implying PR review happens. Gerrit's code-owners plugin is likewise skipped (with one human, everything is owned by them).\n\n## Scope\n\nIN: GOVERNANCE.md, MAINTAINERS.md, CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md contact + version assessment, decision records.\nOUT: CODEOWNERS (either flavor); formal voting machinery (Homebrew/Node scale); a foundation-style CoC committee.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] GOVERNANCE.md present with all seven sections and the Gerrit-mirror reorientation near the top.\n- [ ] MAINTAINERS.md present: table + emeritus placeholder + change process pointer.\n- [ ] CoC enforcement contact is role-based with a named Nava backstop for maintainer-concerning reports.\n- [ ] Three decisions recorded on the ticket: lead-maintainer vs BDFL language; CC 2.1 vs 3.0; CODEOWNERS non-goal rationale.\n- [ ] Open org decisions resolved with Nava before close: (a) succession — whether authority rests with the person or with Nava PBC (PyPI project name, Gerrit host ownership); (b) the named Nava CoC backstop contact.","id":"eb3a-91d4-b1c0-4a37","parent_id":"fc2a-9fa5-def6-4e68","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Publish governance: GOVERNANCE.md, MAINTAINERS.md, CoC contact fix (no CODEOWNERS)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783628672464630001,"uuid":"82199626-4b4c-4c4a-b534-75296462ff86"}